Boil a large #pot of salted water for the rice.

Once boiling, add the @rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pot.

Cover with a #lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(chopped into small pieces).

Place a large #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the oil is hot, add the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g} and half the
chopped onion to the pan with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Fry until chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{2%sachets} to the pan and fry for
~{1%minute}.

Spoon in the @Peanut Butter{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml} (double for 4p).

Mix well and cover. Allow to simmer for ~{4-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove the #pan from the heat and stir in the @Yoghurt{75%g}. Season to taste
with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

== Salad ==

Trim half the @Cucumber{1/2}(quartered lengthways and chopped into small pieces)
(double for 4p) then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Quarter the @Lime{1}(quartered).

Cut the @Tomato{1}(cut into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks.

To a medium #bowl add the cucumber, tomato and remaining chopped onion.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and lime juice.

Stir to combine.

== To Serve ==

Serve the chicken with the salad and rice.

Top with chopped coriander and any remaining lime wedges.